abstract: The U.S. defense agency that handles secure communications for President Donald Trump said Social Security numbers and other personal data in its network may have been compromised, according to letters seen by Reuters on Thursday that were sent to people possibly affected.
snippet: The U.S. defense agency that handles secure communications for President Donald Trump said Social Security numbers and other personal data in its network may have been compromised, according to letters seen by Reuters on Thursday that were sent to...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. defense agency that handles secure communications for President Donald Trump said Social Security numbers and other personal data in its network may have been compromised, according to letters seen by Reuters on Thursday that were sent to people possibly affected.
headline_main: U.S. Agency That Handles Trump's Secure Communication Suffered Data Breach
headline_print_headline: U.S. Agency That Handles Trump's Secure Communication Suffered Data Breach

abstract: Victoria Coates, one of President Donald Trump's longest-serving national security aides, is leaving the White House soon to become a senior adviser at the Energy Department, the White House said on Thursday.
snippet: Victoria Coates, one of President Donald Trump's longest-serving national security aides, is leaving the White House soon to become a senior adviser at the Energy Department, the White House said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Victoria Coates, one of President Donald Trump's longest-serving national security aides, is leaving the White House soon to become a senior adviser at the Energy Department, the White House said on Thursday.
headline_main: Trump's Deputy National Security Adviser Victoria Coates Leaving White House
headline_print_headline: Trump's Deputy National Security Adviser Victoria Coates Leaving White House

abstract: This time it's different. Unlike recent surges, the dollar's  ongoing advance may be handing Europe an export advantage, by driving the euro to three-year lows against trade partners' currencies.
snippet: This time it's different. Unlike recent surges, the dollar's  ongoing advance may be handing Europe an export advantage, by driving the euro to three-year lows against trade partners' currencies.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — This time it's different. Unlike recent surges, the dollar's ongoing advance may be handing Europe an export advantage, by driving the euro to three-year lows against trade partners' currencies.
headline_main: Euro Slump Spreads Far and Wide vs Trading Peers
headline_print_headline: Euro Slump Spreads Far and Wide vs Trading Peers

abstract: Britain and Australia joined the State Department’s effort to deter Moscow from interfering in the 2020 U.S. presidential election.
snippet: Britain and Australia joined the State Department’s effort to deter Moscow from interfering in the 2020 U.S. presidential election.
lead_paragraph: The United States and its key allies on Thursday accused Russia’s main military intelligence agency of a broad cyberattack against the republic of Georgia in October that took out websites and interrupted television broadcasts, in a coordinated effort to deter Moscow from intervening in the 2020 presidential election in the United States.

abstract: A new White House report says the U.S. economy is growing faster than expected, even though the annual gains of 3% that President Donald Trump promised to voters have yet to be achieved.
snippet: A new White House report says the U.S. economy is growing faster than expected, even though the annual gains of 3% that President Donald Trump promised to voters have yet to be achieved.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A new White House report says the U.S. economy is growing faster than expected, even though the annual gains of 3% that President Donald Trump promised to voters have yet to be achieved.
headline_main: WH Report Says Economy Accelerated Under Trump
headline_print_headline: WH Report Says Economy Accelerated Under Trump

abstract: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said on Thursday he was reviving a plan for the construction of 3,000 new settler homes near East Jerusalem, a project effectively frozen after international opposition.
snippet: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said on Thursday he was reviving a plan for the construction of 3,000 new settler homes near East Jerusalem, a project effectively frozen after international opposition.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said on Thursday he was reviving a plan for the construction of 3,000 new settler homes near East Jerusalem, a project effectively frozen after international opposition.
headline_main: Netanyahu Announces Plans for 3,000 New Settler Homes Near East Jerusalem
headline_print_headline: Netanyahu Announces Plans for 3,000 New Settler Homes Near East Jerusalem

abstract: Roger Stone, a longtime confidant of President Donald Trump, was sentenced to more than three years in prison Thursday for obstructing a congressional investigation in a case that has sparked fears about presidential interference in the justice system.
snippet: Roger Stone, a longtime confidant of President Donald Trump, was sentenced to more than three years in prison Thursday for obstructing a congressional investigation in a case that has sparked fears about presidential interference in the justice sy...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Roger Stone, a longtime confidant of President Donald Trump, was sentenced to more than three years in prison Thursday for obstructing a congressional investigation in a case that has sparked fears about presidential interference in the justice system.
headline_main: Trump Ally Roger Stone Sentenced to Over 3 Years in Prison
headline_print_headline: Trump Ally Roger Stone Sentenced to Over 3 Years in Prison

abstract: U.S. energy firm Westinghouse is expected to sign a new agreement with state-run Nuclear Power Corporation of India for the supply of six nuclear reactors during U.S. President Donald Trump's visit next week, officials said, aiming to kickstart a long-running project.
snippet: U.S. energy firm Westinghouse is expected to sign a new agreement with state-run Nuclear Power Corporation of India for the supply of six nuclear reactors during U.S. President Donald Trump's visit next week, officials said, aiming to kickstart a ...
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — U.S. energy firm Westinghouse is expected to sign a new agreement with state-run Nuclear Power Corporation of India for the supply of six nuclear reactors during U.S. President Donald Trump's visit next week, officials said, aiming to kickstart a long-running project.
headline_main: Exclusive: Westinghouse Set to Sign Pact With Indian Firm for Nuclear Reactors During Trump Visit
